<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550338>
    dc:description "FIGURES 196–202. Meri martinique spec. nov. 196–199 male (IBSP 271305, holotype), left palp (196 prolateral, 197 ventral, 198 retrolateral, 199 detail of embolus); 200–202 Female (AMNH, paratype) (200 epigyne, 201 vulva, 202 schematic course of internal duct system). E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6550338/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550350>
    dc:description "FIGURES 221–224. Meri pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov., male (IBSP 20795), left palp (221 prolateral, 222 ventral, 223 retrolateral, 224 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; mr—membranous region; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA— retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; tp—tegular protrusion; vb—ventral branch of RTA. Scale lines: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6550350/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550426>
    dc:description "FIGURES 315–318. Distribution maps for species of Meri gen. nov. 315 (M. martinique spec. nov., M. sanctivincenti (Simon) comb. nov., M. trinitatis (Strand) comb. nov., M. carabobo spec. nov., M. kaieteur spec. nov.); 316 (M. jaraua spec. nov., M. arraijan spec. nov., M. formosus (Banks) comb. nov., M. guri spec. nov., M. tumatumari spec. nov.); 317 (M. zeteki spec. nov., M. manaos spec. nov., M. yaciba spec. nov., M. tapirapeco spec. nov., M. abuna spec. nov.); 318 (M. mathani (Simon) comb. nov., M. pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov., M. conduri spec. nov., M. paiaia spec. nov., M. tambor spec. nov.);" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6550426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550504>
    dc:description "FIGURES 265–268. Meri trinitatis (Strand) comb. nov., male (AMNH), left palp (265 prolateral, 266 ventral, 267 retrolateral, 268 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." ;
